{{Infobox animanga/Header | name = My Girlfriend's a Geek | image = Fujoshi Kanojo Light Novel Volume 1.jpg | image_size = 200px | caption = Cover of the first ''My Girlfriend's a Geek'' light novel | ja_kanji = 腐女子彼女。 | ja_romaji = Fujoshi Kanojo. | genre = [[Comedy]], [[Romance novel|Romance]], [[Slice of life story|Slice of life]] }} {{Infobox animanga/Print | type = light novel | author = [[Pentabu]] | publisher = [[Enterbrain]] | publisher_en = {{English manga publisher|NA=[[Yen Press]]}} | demographic = | imprint = | magazine = | first = December 8, 2006 | last = August 1, 2007 | volumes = 2 | volume_list = }} {{Infobox animanga/Print | type = manga | author = [[Pentabu]] | illustrator = [[Rize Shinba]] | publisher = [[Enterbrain]] | publisher_en = {{English manga publisher|NA=[[Yen Press]]}} | demographic = ''[[Shōjo manga|Shōjo]]'' | magazine = B's LOG Comics | first = December 1, 2007 | last = March 1, 2010 | volumes = 5 | volume_list = }} {{Infobox animanga/Video | type = live film | director = [[Atsushi Kaneshige]] | producer = [[Enterbrain]] | writer = [[Ei Katsuragi]] | music = | studio = | released = {{Start date|2009|05|02}} | runtime = }} {{Infobox animanga/Footer}}
{{Nihongo|'''''My Girlfriend's a Geek'''''|腐女子彼女。|Fujoshi Kanojo.}} is a Japanese [[light novel]] series in two volumes by Pentabu based on a popular [[blog]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://pentabutabu.blog35.fc2.com/ |title=Fujoshi Kanojo at Pentabu's official website|publisher=[[Pentabu]] |accessdate=July 24, 2009|language=Japanese}}</ref> of the same name with 11 million<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mainichi.jp/enta/mantan/news/20090601mog00m200007000c.html|script-title=ja:大東俊介：映画「腐女子彼女。」に主演 間口広く何でも吸収したい 「執事喫茶」も体験|work=[[Mainichi Shimbun]]|language=Japanese|date=June 1, 2009|accessdate=July 25, 2009|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090603163442/http://mainichi.jp/enta/mantan/news/20090601mog00m200007000c.html|archivedate=June 3, 2009|df=}}</ref> page views. A manga adaptation by [[Rize Shinba]] started serialization in 2007 and was published by [[Enterbrain]] under their ''B's LOG Comics'' imprint. A movie adaption was published in 2009 with ''My Geeky Girlfriend'' as the International English title.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt1424056/releaseinfo#akas|title=Fujoshi Kanojo at IMDB's official website|publisher=[[IMDB]] |accessdate=July 24, 2009}}</ref> Both the light novel and manga have been licensed for release by [[Yen Press]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.yenpress.com/?page_id=4 |title=Yen Press: Books |publisher=[[Yen Press]] |accessdate=August 31, 2009}}</ref>
== Story synopsis ==
The story is about the misadventures of a college student, who was falling in love with a pretty girl two years his senior, while in a part-time job, only to find out his girlfriend is a hard-core [[yaoi fangirl]], and so his torment begins.
== Media ==
